<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Enumerate reachable metadata in (almost) post-order.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Enumerate all the metadata reachable from MD.  We want to minimize the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// cost of reading bitcode records, and so the primary consideration is that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// operands of uniqued nodes are resolved before the nodes are read.  This</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// avoids re-uniquing them on the context and factors away RAUW support.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00275" /><CodeLine lineNumber="275"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This algorithm guarantees that subgraphs of uniqued nodes are in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00276" /><CodeLine lineNumber="276"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// post-order.  Distinct subgraphs reachable only from a single uniqued node</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00277" /><CodeLine lineNumber="277"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// will be in post-order.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\note The relative order of a distinct and uniqued node is irrelevant.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\a organizeMetadata() will later partition distinct nodes ahead of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// uniqued ones.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///&#123;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
